    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix PTRS symbol counting in get_ptrs_symbols_in_slot function\n\n### Summary\nThe `get_ptrs_symbols_in_slot` function in ptrs_nr.c was not correctly counting PTRS symbols within the specified range. The loop condition was incorrectly using `i <= nb_symb` instead of `i < start_symb + nb_symb`, causing it to count symbols in the wrong range.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/NR_REFSIG/ptrs_nr.c`: Fixed loop condition in `get_ptrs_symbols_in_slot` function to properly count symbols from `start_symb` for `nb_symb` number of symbols.\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen calling `get_ptrs_symbols_in_slot(ptrsSymPos, start_symbol_index, nr_of_symbols)` with:\n- start_symbol_index = 2 \n- nr_of_symbols = 4\n- ptrsSymPos bitmask indicating PTRS symbols at positions 2, 4, 6\n\nThe function would incorrectly return 2 instead of the expected 2, and more importantly would miss checking symbol 5 in the range. In edge cases where start_symbol_index=0 and nr_of_symbols=2, it would incorrectly check symbols 0,1,2 instead of just 0,1.\n\nThis causes incorrect PTRS symbol counting which affects phase tracking reference signal processing in the 5G NR PHY layer.\n"
}